productName.name: productName
productName.description: Name of ADIC branded product. Uniquely identifies the product, independent of OEM.

productDisplayName.name: productDisplayName
productDisplayName.description: Name of this agent for display purposes. May be customized for OEM.

productDescription.name: productDescription
productDescription.description: A short description of this SNMP agent.

productVendor.name: productVendor
productVendor.description: Name of the product vendor or OEM.

productVersion.name: productVersion
productVersion.description: String Format: MNNO.TVBBBPP Examples 1. 091a.TR054 Version 0.91, build 54 of the RCS test code for ADIC 2. 100A.GM052 Version 1.00, build 52 of the MCB GA candidate code for ADIC M Major version number NN Minor version number O OEM (Uppercase when release candidate, otherwise lowercase) A/a - ADIC Others - Reserved) T Target G - GA Candidate Release (labeled build that is a release candidate) T - Test build (labeled build used for formal testing) D - Dev build (labeled build used for unit testing) (lower case) - specifies developer of a local build V Variant S - System R - RCS M - MCB BBB Build number (3 digit sequential number specifying exact build) PP Patch Number (Optional alphanumeric characters denoting patch level of this build if necessary)

productDisplayVersion.name: productDisplayVersion
productDisplayVersion.description: The version identifier according to the vendor or OEM.

productLibraryClass.name: productLibraryClass
productLibraryClass.description: Basic library includes minimal connectivity hardware. Intelligent library includes SAN appliances and value-added features.

productSerialNumber.name: productSerialNumber
productSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the entire library.

agentGlobalStatus.name: agentGlobalStatus
agentGlobalStatus.description: Current overall status of the agent.

agentLastGlobalStatus.name: agentLastGlobalStatus
agentLastGlobalStatus.description: The status before the current status which induced an initiative to issue a global status change trap.

agentTimeStamp.name: agentTimeStamp
agentTimeStamp.description: The last time that the agent values have been updated. Universal time in seconds since UTC 1/1/70.

agentGetTimeOut.name: agentGetTimeOut
agentGetTimeOut.description: Suggested time out in milliseconds for how long an SNMP management application should wait while attempting to poll the SNMP agent.

agentModifiers.name: agentModifiers
agentModifiers.description: Agent functional modifiers, when set the modifier is active. ----------------------------------------------------- Bit 3 => Agent in debug mode. ----------------------------------------------------- All other bits are product specific.

agentRefreshRate.name: agentRefreshRate
agentRefreshRate.description: Rate in seconds at which the agent cached data is being updated.

componentTable.name: componentTable
componentTable.description: General information about the system's components, including the unique identifiers. The structure this table is based on the Fibre Alliance MIB connUnitEntry.

componentEntry.name: componentEntry
componentEntry.description: A component entry containing objects for a particular component.

componentId.name: componentId
componentId.description: The unique identification for this component among those within this proxy domain.

componentDisplayName.name: componentDisplayName
componentDisplayName.description: Name of this component for display purposes. Different OEMs may have different display names for the same ADIC product.

componentInfo.name: componentInfo
componentInfo.description: A display string containing information about this component.

componentSn.name: componentSn
componentSn.description: The serial number for this component.

componentControl.name: componentControl
componentControl.description: This object is used to control the addressed connUnit. NOTE: 'Cold Start' and 'Warm Start' are as defined in MIB II and are not meant to be a factory reset. resetColdStart: the addressed unit performs a 'Cold Start' reset. resetWarmStart: the addressed unit performs a 'Warm Start' reset. offline: the addressed unit puts itself into an implementation dependant 'offline' state. online: the addressed unit puts itself into an implementation dependant 'online' state.

componentREDId.name: componentREDId
componentREDId.description: Runtime Error Detection identifier for this power supply.

componentFirmwareVersion.name: componentFirmwareVersion
componentFirmwareVersion.description: Firmware version (or level) for this component.

componentGeoAddrAisle.name: componentGeoAddrAisle
componentGeoAddrAisle.description: The aisle number where this component is located. A negative value indicates that an aisle number is not applicable to this component.

componentGeoAddrFrame.name: componentGeoAddrFrame
componentGeoAddrFrame.description: The frame number where this component is located. A negative value indicates that a frame number is not applicable to this component.

componentGeoAddrRack.name: componentGeoAddrRack
componentGeoAddrRack.description: The rack number where this component is located. A negative value indicates that a rack number is not applicable to this component.

componentGeoAddrChassis.name: componentGeoAddrChassis
componentGeoAddrChassis.description: The chassis number where this component is located. A negative value indicates that a chassis number is not applicable to this component.

componentGeoAddrBlade.name: componentGeoAddrBlade
componentGeoAddrBlade.description: The blade number within the network chasis where this component is located. A negative value indicates that a blade number is not applicable to this component.

componentIpAddress.name: componentIpAddress
componentIpAddress.description: IP address of this component. If the component has no IP address, this object returns 0.0.0.0. The address may refer to an internal network not accessible to an external management application.

trapIntendedUsage.name: trapIntendedUsage
trapIntendedUsage.description: The value of this qualifier aids the management application in determining how to respond to the trap. If the value is public(1), the information is intended to be propagated to external observers, such as sending email. If the value is triggerRefresh(2), the information is intended to update the management application's data model, but not necessarily propagated to external observers.
